=== 13.2 Multi-Query and Grouped-Query Attention

Standard multi-head attention (Chapter 7) creates separate stem:[Q, K, V] projections for every head.
The key and value matrices dominate GPU memory during inference.

*Multi-Query Attention (MQA)* (Shazeer, 2019) uses a single stem:[K] and stem:[V] shared across all heads, reducing the KV cache by a factor of stem:[H] (number of heads).

*Grouped-Query Attention (GQA)* (Ainslie et al., 2023) is a middle ground: stem:[G] groups of heads share a single stem:[K, V], where stem:[1 \leq G \leq H].
Setting stem:[G=1] recovers MQA; setting stem:[G=H] recovers standard MHA.

[cols="1,1,1,1", options="header"]
|===
| Method | KV heads | Memory | Quality

| MHA | H | 1x | Baseline
| GQA | H/G | 1/G x | Near-MHA
| MQA | 1 | 1/H x | Slight drop
|===

GQA is used in LLaMA 3, Mistral, and Gemma.
It allows inference to fit in less memory without significant quality degradation.
